{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Summary\nBuild the FOUNDATION of epic 3006-e198: the pure classifier, the per-binding baseline, the decision-census telemetry, the circuit breaker, and the test harness. This ticket wires NOTHING into the live pass (the four drift-class bugs and the rollout task consume it). All invariants are specified by ADRs 0026-0029 (docs/adr/) — read them FIRST.\n\n## New module: src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/classify.py (pure leaf; no I/O, no imports from differ/outbound_differ/inbound_differ)\n- `class ObservedJira(Enum): PRESENT | CONFIRMED_404 | ABSENT_IN_WINDOW | TRANSPORT_ERROR` — the four-way observation state of ADR 0028 (NEVER a boolean; ABSENT_IN_WINDOW must never be treated as deleted).\n- `class LocalState(Enum): ACTIVE | TERMINAL | ABSENT` — TERMINAL = local status in {archived, deleted} or archived flag.\n- `@dataclass(frozen=True) class Decision: kind: DecisionKind; reason: str; payload: dict` — kind is a CLOSED enum: `SYNC_FIELDS | ADOPT | TERMINAL_TRANSITION | PROBE_GET | RETIRE_AFTER_GRACE | SKIP_RETIRED | ALERT | NOOP`.\n- `def classify(local: dict|None, jira: ObservedJira-tagged snapshot value, binding: dict|None, baseline: dict|None) -> Decision` — the FULL (LocalState x ObservedJira x binding-present) matrix, every cell explicitly enumerated (no default-else fallthrough: unmatched cell raises).\n- Matrix anchor cells (must match the 2026-07-03 spike + the child bugs): bound+ACTIVE+PRESENT -> SYNC_FIELDS; bound+TERMINAL+PRESENT(not Done) -> TERMINAL_TRANSITION; bound+*+ABSENT_IN_WINDOW -> PROBE_GET; bound+*+CONFIRMED_404 (grace met) -> RETIRE_AFTER_GRACE; bound+*+TRANSPORT_ERROR -> NOOP(defer); unbound+PRESENT+retired -> SKIP_RETIRED; unbound+PRESENT -> ADOPT; bound+ABSENT-local -> ALERT.\n\n## Per-binding baseline (ADR 0026 — read its 4 decision points verbatim)\n- Extend the bindings.json entry (binding_store.py, `BindingStore`): add `baseline: {summary, description, priority, status, assignee}` + `baseline_advanced_at`; bump the file `version` field; older entries without baseline are VALID (absent baseline degrades to local-wins per ADR 0026 #2).\n- New methods `get_baseline(local_id) -> dict|None`, `set_baseline(local_id, fields: dict)`; persisted by the existing `save()` + committed by the existing `_commit_binding_store_snapshot` (reconcile.py) — no new commit path.\n- One-shot seed helper `seed_baselines_from_snapshot(prev_snapshot: dict)` — sets a baseline for every bound key present in the snapshot (derisk X4 proved all 613 bound+present keys carry all 5 fields). Do NOT delete prev_snapshot or change its consumers in this ticket.\n- Corrupt bindings.json stays FAIL-CLOSED (existing behavior); do not weaken it.\n\n## Circuit breaker (pure function here; live wiring is the rollout task)\n- `def check_blast_radius(decisions: Iterable[Decision], total_bindings: int, max_acting_fraction: float) -> BreakerVerdict` in classify.py or a sibling `breaker.py`; acting kinds = {TERMINAL_TRANSITION, RETIRE_AFTER_GRACE, ADOPT}; config key `reconciler.max_acting_fraction` default 0.10 (2026-07-03 census measured 1.14% acting — 8.8x headroom).\n\n## Decision-census telemetry (approved remediation 1)\n- `def census(decisions) -> dict` returning {counts-by-kind, acting_count, acting_pct, breaker_verdict}; emitted via the existing `SyncLogger.log(\"decision_census\", **census)` (sync_logger.py) — the emit call itself lands with the first consumer, but the record shape + unit test land HERE.\n\n## Tests (approved remediation 3 included)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/classify/test_matrix.py — table test: EVERY matrix cell, incl. the ADR 0028 regression cells (Done-beyond-cap -> PROBE_GET not RETIRE; transport-error -> NOOP).\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/classify/test_properties.py — hypothesis: (a) convergence: apply decisions to a model world, re-classify -> zero acting; (b) no-orphan; (c) conservation (no double-bind); (d) direction-preservation: a Jira-side edit with local==baseline is never pushed outbound (ADR 0026 consequence).\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/classify/test_frozen_census.py — replay sanitized frozen fixtures (tests/fixtures/bridge_convergence/frozen-2026-07-03/: bindings.json + snapshot skeleton, PII/body-stripped) asserting EXACTLY 7 acting decisions (5x TERMINAL_TRANSITION REB-464/456/465/466/457, 1x PROBE_GET REB-530, 1x ADOPT REB-532) then fixed-point after simulated heal.\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/state/test_binding_baseline.py — get/set/seed/version-compat/corrupt-fail-closed.\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/classify/test_multipass_stateful.py — the epic's multi-pass stateful + fault-injection cell: a model world driven through N passes where the baseline is PERSISTED to a real temp bindings.json between passes (the faithful-persistence gap that hid drift class B); inject partial-apply failure (a Decision's apply raises mid-pass) and assert the NEXT pass re-derives the same Decision and self-heals to the fixed point.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] classify.py exists as a pure leaf module (no reconciler imports) with the closed Decision enum and the fully-enumerated matrix; unmatched cells raise.\n- [ ] Baseline field + get/set/seed on BindingStore; absent baseline degrades local-wins; corrupt store still fails closed; version bumped with back-compat read.\n- [ ] check_blast_radius + census implemented with unit tests; config key `reconciler.max_acting_fraction` (default 0.10) registered in the typed config schema (_config_schema.py).\n- [ ] All five test files above pass; frozen-census fixture checked in (sanitized); hypothesis suite includes the four named properties; the multi-pass test persists the baseline through a real file between passes and asserts self-heal after injected partial failure.\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make test` green; no file exceeds the 800 LOC soft cap."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783105955027808001,"uuid":"c2b0e129-0ba3-4861-bc25-a07a24dbc2d1"}